"{\"uid\": \"29news.com-2024-08-29-albemarle-police-raises-funds-special-olympics\", \"text\": \"ALBEMARLE COUNTY, Va. (WVIR) - Members of the Albemarle County Police Department are raising money for the Special Olympics.  The week-long initiative is called Cover the Cruiser.  Those who donate can write a note of encouragement for athletes. Each day Albemarle Police takes the notes and, just like the name says, covers one of their cruisers with each message.  \\\"What we want to do is give back to the community and we have a lot of local athletes that participate in Special Olympics,\\\" ACPD Officer David Sprouse said. \\\"This is a way for us to give back and we get to interact with people on a regular basis throughout the week.\\\"  Albemarle Police will be at the Wawa on Seminole trail Friday, August 30, for the last day of the fundraiser.  Do you have a story idea? Send us your news tiphere.  Copyright 2024 WVIR. All rights reserved.\"}"